| 0.992057 | -48 | Microscope picks up structure 96 ULP wide |
| 0.997488 | -224 | |
| 0.999000 | -752 | |
| 0.999684 | +9,664 | |
| 0.999900 | -65,536 | |
| 0.999937 | +18,112 | |
| **0.999950** | **-166,272** | |
| **0.999960** | **-100,096** | |
| **β → 1** | **up to ±505,856** | F4 preserves signal that's invisible to F1/F2/F3 |

ARM-W (F2) remains `below_floor` everywhere past β ≈ 0.85 — the wide lens has been silent for 50+ records. ARM-N (F4) continues to read structured signal all the way to β=0.999999..., and the magnitudes are not noise but signal that scales with proximity to the singularity. **The microscope has measurement headroom that the wide lens does not.**

Many of these densified records are tagged `agreement_v11 = underpowered` because ARM-W is invalid (below_floor). This is correct: there's no overlap with ARM-W in this region — ARM-N is operating solo. The 6 + 1 overlap pattern is preserved unchanged because the overlap region itself didn't densify; only the post-overlap singularity zone did.

